    "course_title": "CULTURAL PSYCHOLOGY",
    "description": "Societies are shaped by the people, places, and environments that surround us. Examine the ways that culture and individual psychology make each other up, including how we think about ourselves, how we attend to and reason about the world, how we think about those like us and unlike us, and how these beliefs, attitudes, and cognitions are shared and maintained across groups.",
